      "agentResultText": "Done. Here's what was added:\n\n**`src/lib/db/queries.ts`** — New `moveTask(taskId, fromProjectId, toProjectId)` function that uses `db.transaction()` to atomically verify the task belongs to the source project, verify the destination project exists, then update `tasks.projectId`. If either check fails, the transaction rolls back.\n\n**`src/app/api/projects/[id]/tasks/[taskId]/move/route.ts`** — Replaced the 501 stub. Accepts `POST` with `{ targetProjectId }` body, validates input, calls `moveTask()`, returns the updated task or a 400/404 error.\n\n**`src/components/move-task-button.tsx`** — New `\"use client\"` component. Shows a \"Move\" button per task row. Clicking it reveals a dropdown of other projects. Selecting one calls the move API endpoint and refreshes the page via `router.refresh()`.\n\n**`src/app/projects/[id]/page.tsx`** — Added an \"Actions\" column to the task table with `MoveTaskButton` in each row, passing the full project list.",
